      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>604 threads, <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=0>1</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=25>2</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=50>3</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=75>4</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=100>5</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=125>6</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=150>7</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=175>8</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=200>9</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=225>10</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=250>11</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=275>12</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=300>13</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=325>14</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=350>15</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=375>16</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=400>17</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=425>18</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=450>19</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=475>20</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=500>21</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=525>22</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=550>23</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=575>24</a> <a href=classes.html?class=7&start=600>25</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=classes.html?class=7&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98132666515254></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98132666515254><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Important Notes for Clerics and others</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 4th 10:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a level 52 Dwarf Cleric.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's not my highest char but it is one of the more fun ones to play with.  I really enjoy how Clerics are so valued in groups.  I rarely sit idle for more than 10 minutes before being invited somewhere and that's refreshing.<br><br>On the other hand, I've noticed that many people do not understand the role of a cleric or are somewhat naive about what clerics can and should do.  Here is my .02cp on the issues:<br><br>* A good cleric will make hot-keys for his heals, and announce to the group what he's casting, on whom, and most importantly, how long it will take (i.e. "Casting superior heal on %T - ETA 4.5sec")  which lets group members know that the cleric is engaged with one spell and cannot be available to immediately heal on a second member<br><br>* IMO, if there is a secondary healer in the group, it is his responsibility to keep the cleric healed.  It's bad if the cleric has to heal himself if a secondary healer can take care of that.<br><br>* Don't use Celestial Healing on casters - it's a wonderful spell for tanks, but doesn't heal fast enough, quick enough to be of great use on those without a lot of hp.  I generally will lay down a Cel on any tank that has 2 bubs of health gone.  The exception to this rule is a warrior, whom I'll do my best to let go beserk before I lay down a Cheal.  If you have tanks in your group, you'll find that Cel is far better than superior heal: faster, cheaper, more healing.<br><br>* Clerics have another ability which in many ways is even more effective than healing, and that is STUNNING.  If you're in a good group, you generally should only need to heal for certain situations (large pull, enchanter gets beat up, etc.) otherwise you can chain stun the mobs and keep them from hitting the group in the first place and negate the need for any major heals.  Being a dwarf, I can tank pretty darn well and am exceptionally effective at keeping the mobs from doing damage in the first place.  All I need to kick arse is a tank with a good taunt.<br><br>Here are some hints for grouping with a cleric:<br><br>* If you're getting beat up, don't run off.  This is one of the biggest hassels clerics have is casting on someone and then having them go out of range.  If you want to run to save your life, by all means, do so, but either announce you're zoning, or run around the cleric so he can heal you.<br><br>* If you're a shaman or necro, and cannibalize yourself for mana, do NOT expect the cleric to heal you!  That's selfish and it's not an efficient use of the cleric's mana.<br><br>* Don't expect to be healed to full if you're in a tight situation.  I generally do not have anything less than Superior Heal mem'd so I won't heal anyone except maybe a lightweight caster, past 1bub of health unless i have plenty of mana.  Obviously the strategy varies dending upon the level, zone and party configuration.<br><br>* If you're a shaman or druid, REGEN THE TANKS!  Don't assume that just because a cleric is in the group that you don't have to be responsible for any healing whatsoever.  Having the tanks chloro'd makes the cleric a thousand times more effective.<br><br>* If you die, it's your fault - not the cleric's.  I'm sick and tired of tanks fighting like they're invulnerable long after the cleric has announced he's out of mana.  Sometimes things happen so fast it's nearly impossible to save somebody.  Also for enchanters, unless someone is messing with your mezzes, don't blame the cleric if you're getting stingy with your crowd control casting and get jumped and then get pissed because the cleric couldn't get his 5 second heal off in 2 to save your butt.<br><br>* If it's your responsibility, know when to call EVAC or ZONE.  More groups perish because the leader doesn't know when to quit than all of the healer problem issues combined.  And even in that situation, the healer will try to stay around and make sure everyone gets out ok.<br><br>* Nothing is more frustrating than to have a low-level tank in a high level group.  These PCs might as well hook up a mana siphon to the cleric because that's all he's going to do, constantly healing the too-low-a-level-to-be-in-this-place tank.  Please try to group with players your own level so as to not put undue stress on the group.<br><br>I could go on, but hopefully you will find some of this helpful.  People wonder why sometimes clerics have attitudes - I haven't even addressed the constant res/heal request issues; it's tough enough getting into a group and having everyone look at you like you killed Old Yeller if they die under virtually any circumstance.  Yes, there are good clerics and bad clerics, and we know what our job is, but staying alive is a coordinated, group effort.<br><br> - G<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
